						<summary>

						<p>East wall of the Subrahmaṇya shrine in the Nāgēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājēndrachōḷa I, Year 8: 1019-20 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete and damaged record commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Tirumaṉṉi-vaḷara,</hi> etc., of the king.</p>						

						<p>This seems to record a grant for food offerings and lamps during the three <hi rend="italic">sandhis</hi> to the god Chandraśēkaradēva set up by Vēḷāṉ Malli <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Uṇṇānaṅgai, probably in the temple of Tirukkīḻk-kōṭṭam-uḍaiyamahādēva in Tirukkuḍamukku in Pāmbūr-nāḍu in Uy[ya*]koṇḍār-vaḷanāḍu. Other details are lost as it is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
